The paper discusses the failure of forecast strategies when applied to complicated time series, and proposes a method to measure complexity and predictive structure in experimental time series. This suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI), as well as statistics (cs.ST) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the use of permutation entropy as a measure of complexity and predictability suggests a potential connection to signal processing and control theory (cs.SI).
